-- Alstom says to review GE offer for energy business
-- By James Regan
-- Wed Apr 30, 2014 01:12AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, April 30 (Reuters) - Alstom <ALSO.PA> said on Wednesday that it would review a proposed bid from General Electric <GE.N> for its energy business by the end of May.

The offer price gives Alstom's thermal power, renewable power and grid businesses an enterprise value of 11.4 billion euros ($15.75 billion), the company said.